  "prompt": "Is there a way to sort by the most upvoted answers on Quora?",
  "response": "As of my knowledge cutoff in October 2023, Quora does not have a built-in feature to sort answers specifically by the most upvoted. However, you can use the following methods to find highly upvoted answers:\n\n1. **Default Sorting**: Quora often surfaces answers with more upvotes higher in the default view, so the top answers on a question page are typically among the most upvoted.\n\n2. **Search for Popular Answers**: Use Quora's search bar to find answers related to a specific topic. Popular or highly upvoted answers may appear at the top of the search results.\n\n3. **Quora Digest**: Check Quora Digest emails or the \"Answers\" section on Quora, as they often highlight popular or trending answers.\n\n4. **Third-Party Tools**: Some external tools or scripts (e.g., browser extensions) may allow you to sort or filter answers by upvotes, though these are not officially supported by Quora.\n\nIf Quora has introduced new features since October 2023, I recommend checking their help center or announcements for updates on sorting options.",
